'''含糖飲料稅'''或'''汽水稅'''是為了打擊含有[[游離糖|游離糖]]的飲料消費量的[[稅|稅]]或附加費。其涵蓋範圍通常包括[[碳酸飲料|碳酸飲料]]、[[非碳酸飲料|非碳酸飲料]]、[[運動飲料|運動飲料]]及[[能量飲料|能量飲料]]。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://healthyeatingresearch.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/HER-Sports-Drinks-Research-Review-6-2012.pdf|title=Consumption of Sports Drinks by Children and Adolescents|accessdate=18 March 2016|website=Healthy Eating Research|archive-date=2019-06-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190621223007/http://healthyeatingresearch.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/HER-Sports-Drinks-Research-Review-6-2012.pdf|dead-url=no}}</ref>

這種稅在許多地區是公眾論辯議題，[[可口可樂公司|可口可樂公司]]等飲料公司通常都持反對意見。倡議者如國家醫療機構或[[世界卫生组织|世界卫生组织]]都宣傳這種稅是[[庇古税|庇古税]]的一種範例，專門減少[[均衡飲食|不均衡的飲食]]與平衡[[肥胖症|肥胖症所帶來的大量支出]]。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/12/health/sugar-drink-tax-world-health-organization.html?_r=0|title=W.H.O. urges Tax on Sugary Drinks to Fight Obesity|date=11 October 2016|publisher=New York Times|accessdate=8 November 2016|last1=Tavernise|first1=Sabrina|archive-date=2020-09-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200930192410/https://www.nytimes.com/2016/10/12/health/sugar-drink-tax-world-health-organization.html?_r=0|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 背景 ==
[[糖尿病|糖尿病]]是一個在世界各地漸受關注的健康議題；[[2012年|2012年]]內全球就有150萬人直接死於該病症。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.who.int/mediacentre/factsheets/fs312/en/|title=Diabetes Fact Sheet|publisher=World Health Organisation|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2013-08-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130826174444/http://www.who.int/mediacentre/factsheets/fs312/en/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 不像普通食品中的[[糖分|糖分]]，飲料中的糖分會被快速吸收進人體內部，並會造成[[胰臟|胰臟]]及[[肝臟|肝臟]]負荷超量，長久下來將促成糖尿病和[[心血管疾病|心血管疾病]]。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sugarscience.org/sugar-sweetened-beverages/#.WCJFy6OZORs|title=Sugar-Sweetened Beverages|publisher=University of California, San Francisco|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2016-12-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161203140838/http://www.sugarscience.org/sugar-sweetened-beverages/#.WCJFy6OZORs|dead-url=no}}</ref>

[[肥胖症|肥胖症]]也是一個全球性的[[公共卫生|公眾及衛生政策]]之關注所在，因為許多中等收入及以[[发展中国家|開發中地區]]的肥胖及過重人口比例都正在迅速成長。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.who.int/topics/obesity/en/|title=Health Topics, Obesity|publisher=World Health Organisation|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2019-04-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190418110956/https://www.who.int/topics/obesity/en/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 

含[[添加糖|添加糖]]飲料的攝取量已被證實與高量[[食物熱量|卡路里]]之攝取有正向關聯，而體重過重及肥胖亦將伴隨發生。<ref name="AllenPrentice2012">{{cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=OqcL6JgTUf8C&pg=PA231|title=Encyclopedia of Human Nutrition 3E|date=28 December 2012|publisher=Academic Press|accessdate=4 April 2013|isbn=978-0-12-384885-7|pages=231–233|author1=Lindsay H Allen|author2=Andrew Prentice|archive-date=2020-02-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200201072914/https://books.google.com/books?id=OqcL6JgTUf8C&pg=PA231|dead-url=no}}</ref>添加糖常在[[加工食品|加工或即用食品]]中見到，如[[穀物片|早餐穀物片]]、<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.forbes.com/sites/alicegwalton/2014/05/15/all-sugared-up-the-best-and-worst-breakfast-cereals-for-kids/#71e461625836|title=All Sugared Up: The Best And Worst Breakfast Cereals For Kids|date=15 May 2014|publisher=Forbes|last1=Walton|first1=Alice|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2020-11-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201129000745/https://www.forbes.com/sites/alicegwalton/2014/05/15/all-sugared-up-the-best-and-worst-breakfast-cereals-for-kids/#71e461625836|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[巧克力|巧克力]]、[[冰淇淋|冰淇淋]]、[[餅乾|餅乾]]、[[酸奶|酸奶]]及各種市面上的[[飲品|飲品]]。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ft.com/intl/cms/s/0/62bc4138-eb85-11e5-888e-2eadd5fbc4a4.html#axzz433ffUgFN|title=The Budget’s sugar tax is half-baked|date=16 March 2016|publisher=Financial Times|last1=Harford|first1=Tim|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2022-02-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220219051726/https://www.ft.com/content/62bc4138-eb85-11e5-888e-2eadd5fbc4a4#axzz433ffUgFN|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.theguardian.com/business/2016/feb/17/cafe-chains-selling-drinks-25-teaspoons-sugar-starbucks-costa-coffee|title=The cafes serving drinks with 25 teaspoons of sugar per cup|date=17 February 2016|publisher=The Guardian|last1=Brignall|first1=Miles|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112040409/https://www.theguardian.com/business/2016/feb/17/cafe-chains-selling-drinks-25-teaspoons-sugar-starbucks-costa-coffee|dead-url=no}}</ref> 以含糖飲料之普及性和年輕消費者對它們的喜愛促使其攝取成為公共衛生專家特別關注的議題。在[[美國|美國]]及[[聯合王國|聯合王國]]，甜飲是[[青少年|青少年]]人群飲食中卡路里攝取量最大的來源。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hsph.harvard.edu/nutritionsource/healthy-drinks/sugary-drinks/#ref34|title=The Nutrition Source: Sugary Drinks|publisher=Harvard School of Public Health|website=Harvard T.H. Chan School of Public Health|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2020-12-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201223132100/https://www.hsph.harvard.edu/nutritionsource/healthy-drinks/sugary-drinks/#ref34|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/health-35824071|title=Sugar tax: How it will work?|date=16 March 2016|publisher=BBC News Online|accessdate=22 March 2016|last1=Triggle|first1=Nick|archive-date=2020-09-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200921135200/https://www.bbc.com/news/health-35824071|dead-url=no}}</ref>

多股趨勢顯現出許多[[已開發國家|已開發經濟體]]對傳統[[汽水|汽水]]的攝取量正在減少，但是中度收入經濟體（如[[越南|越南]]及[[印度|印度]]）的攝取量正在迅速增長中。在美國，也就是[[碳酸飲料|碳酸飲料]]的單一最大市場，消費者人均年蘇打購買水平為154升。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.npr.org/sections/goatsandsoda/2015/06/19/415223346/guess-which-country-has-the-biggest-increase-in-soda-drinking|title=Guess Which Country Has The Biggest Increase In Soda Drinking|date=19 June 2015|publisher=National Public Radio|last1=Silver|first1=Marc|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2020-08-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200817043545/https://www.npr.org/sections/goatsandsoda/2015/06/19/415223346/guess-which-country-has-the-biggest-increase-in-soda-drinking|dead-url=no}}</ref>

[[法国|法國]]於2012年向[[軟性飲料|軟飲料]]徵收糖稅，是首批執行此類政策的國家之一。<ref name="Sparks">{{cite news|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2045980/France-impose-fat-tax-sugary-drinks-Coca-Cola-Fanta.html|title=France to impose fat tax on drinks with added sugar such as Coca-Cola and Fanta|last=Sparks|first=Ian|date=6 October 2011|work=Daily Mail|location=London|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2020-10-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201023224530/https://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2045980/France-impose-fat-tax-sugary-drinks-Coca-Cola-Fanta.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 在國家層級的政治體中，類似的措施亦在[[墨西哥|墨西哥]]宣布於[[2013年|2013年]]，還有聯合王國於2016年。在2014年11月，[[伯克利|加州的柏克利]]成為美國境內首個通過針對汽水徵稅的[[共同體|共同體]]。

=== 菸草稅 ===
汽水稅的支持者總是引用菸草稅在全球的成功案例來解釋汽水稅之可行性。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2010/02/14/weekinreview/14bittman.html|title=Is Soda the New Tobacco?|date=12 February 2010|publisher=The New York Times|last1=Bittman|first1=Mark|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2020-12-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201208091222/https://www.nytimes.com/2010/02/14/weekinreview/14bittman.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>與[[菸草|菸草]]相關的主要問題是[[癌症|癌症]]；而與汽水相關的主要問題則是糖尿病及肥胖。菸草產業對菸草稅之反對與汽水產業對汽水稅之反對有諸多相似之處，包括以贊助研究來顯現其產品之低度健康風險。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/big-soda-is-fighting-science-on-sugar-2015-11|title=Is Soda the New Tobacco?|date=16 November 2015|publisher=Business Insider|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108142632/https://www.businessinsider.com/big-soda-is-fighting-science-on-sugar-2015-11|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 國家 ==

=== 丹麥 ===
[[丹麥|丹麥]]於1930年代創立了一個汽水稅(其稅率相當於1.64丹麥克朗每升)，但於2013年宣布將廢止其與另一同樣不受歡迎的脂肪稅，以製造工作機會並振興經濟。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foodnavigator.com/Legislation/Denmark-to-scrap-decades-old-soft-drink-tax|title=Denmark to scrap decades-old soft drink tax|last1=Scott-Thomas|first1=Caroline|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2013-10-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131022042431/http://www.foodnavigator.com/Legislation/Denmark-to-scrap-decades-old-soft-drink-tax|dead-url=no}}</ref> 批評者聲稱這些稅明顯無效；當地[[零售商|零售商]]抱怨丹麥人為了避免脂肪稅和糖份稅而到[[瑞典|瑞典]]和[[德國|德國]]購買價格較低的[[黃油|黃油]]、冰淇淋和[[蘇打水|蘇打水]]。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2012/11/13/business/global/fat-tax-in-denmark-is-repealed-after-criticism.html|title='Fat Tax’ in Denmark Is Repealed After Criticism|date=12 November 2012|publisher=The New York Times|last1=Strom|first1=Stephanie|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112012212/http://www.nytimes.com/2012/11/13/business/global/fat-tax-in-denmark-is-repealed-after-criticism.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 丹麥於2013年1月廢除脂肪稅，並於2014年廢除軟飲料稅。

=== 法國 ===
[[法国|法國]]首度於2012年以國家層級引進針對含糖飲料的稅法；<ref name="Sparks"/> 隨之而來將是軟性飲料至多3.5%的漲價幅度。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.spiegel.de/wirtschaft/soziales/0,1518,806143,00.html|title=[Controversial sugar levy: France introduces a cola tax]|last=|first=|date=28 December 2011|work=Der Spiegel|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2012-04-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120430232142/http://www.spiegel.de/wirtschaft/soziales/0,1518,806143,00.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=Coca-Cola part en guerre contre la "taxe sodas"|url=http://www.lemonde.fr/politique/article/2011/09/08/coca-cola-part-en-guerre-contre-la-taxe-sodas_1569497_823448.html|year=2011|journal=Le Monde|accessdate=2011-12-30|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111184149/https://www.lemonde.fr/politique/article/2011/09/08/coca-cola-part-en-guerre-contre-la-taxe-sodas_1569497_823448.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 市場研究公司Canadean分析發現軟飲料的銷售量在引入該稅後一年內下降，但接著便連年增長。<ref name="Bouckley2013">{{cite news|url=http://www.beveragedaily.com/Markets/Soft-drinks-stall-in-France-as-consumers-trade-down-Canadean|title=Soft drinks stall in France as consumers trade down: Canadean|date=24 April 2013|work=BeverageDaily.com|publisher=illiam Reed Business Media|accessdate=1 April 2016|last1=Bouckley|first1=Ben|archive-date=2017-09-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170928064052/http://www.beveragedaily.com/Markets/Soft-drinks-stall-in-France-as-consumers-trade-down-Canadean|dead-url=no}}</ref> 然而，該稅適用於含有添加糖的飲料和含有人造甜味劑的飲料，<ref name="Bouckley2013"/><ref name="Economist2015">{{cite news|url=http://www.economist.com/news/finance-and-economics/21679259-taxes-fizzy-drinks-seem-work-intended-stopping-slurping|title=Stopping slurping. Taxes on fizzy drinks seem to work as intended|date=28 November 2015|work=The Economist|accessdate=1 April 2016|archive-date=2018-03-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180313172821/https://www.economist.com/news/finance-and-economics/21679259-taxes-fizzy-drinks-seem-work-intended-stopping-slurping|dead-url=no}}</ref> 可能因此限制了其對蘇打產品的健康性的影響。<ref name="Economist2015"/>

=== 匈牙利 ===
匈牙利的稅法於2011年9月生效，22％的人減少能量飲料消費，19％的人減少了含糖軟飲料的攝入量。<ref name="editor">{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2016/mar/18/sugar-tax-financially-regressive-but-progressive-for-health|title=Sugar tax: financially regressive but progressive for health?|last=editor|first=Denis Campbell Health policy|date=2016-03-17|newspaper=The Guardian|accessdate=2016-08-10|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|archive-date=2020-11-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201127184515/https://www.theguardian.com/society/2016/mar/18/sugar-tax-financially-regressive-but-progressive-for-health|dead-url=no}}</ref>

