=== 英國 ===
在2016年的聯合王國預算中，聯合王國政府宣布將對軟飲料產業課徵糖稅。 計劃將於2018年生效，飲料製造商將根據其生產或進口的增甜飲料的數量徵稅。 稅收的總水平尚未公佈，但估計每年將產生額外5.2億英鎊的稅收，這將在聯合王國用於其初級學校的體育運動資金。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/health-and-families/health-news/budget-2016-george-osborne-announces-sugar-tax-a6934206.html|title=Budget 2016: George Osborne announces sugar tax on soft drinks industry|date=17 March 2016|publisher=The Independent|last1=Gander|first1=Kashmira|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111195421/https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/health-and-families/health-news/budget-2016-george-osborne-announces-sugar-tax-a6934206.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

該法建議純果汁、乳製品飲料和最小的生產商將不被徵稅。 稅金將在生產或進口時在兩個頻帶徵收。 預計每100毫升5克以上的總糖含量將以每升18磅的水平徵稅，每100毫升的飲料超過8克，每升24磅。 預計一些製造商將減少其產品含糖量以避免稅收。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-35824071|title=Sugar tax: How it will work?|date=16 March 2016|publisher=BBC News|accessdate=18 April 2016|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112020220/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-35824071|dead-url=no}}</ref>

在英國關於現代飲食中過量糖的影響的顯著研究包括John Yudkin教授的著作''Pure，White and Deadly：The Problem of Sugar''，一本於1972年首次出版的書。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2016/apr/07/the-sugar-conspiracy-robert-lustig-john-yudkin|title=The sugar conspiracy|date=7 April 2016|newspaper=The Guardian|accessdate=15 November 2016|deadurl=no|last1=Leslie|first1=Ian|archive-date=2016-04-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160407124239/https://www.theguardian.com/society/2016/apr/07/the-sugar-conspiracy-robert-lustig-john-yudkin}}</ref> 關於擬議的含糖飲料稅，2013年10月31日在[[英國醫學期刊|英國醫學期刊]]上發表的一項研究假定，對含糖飲料徵收20％的稅率會使英國的肥胖率降低約1.3％， 結論是，對含糖飲料徵稅是“瞄准人口肥胖，特別是年輕人中的人口肥胖的一種有希望的人口措施」。<ref>{{Cite journal|title=Overall and income specific effect on prevalence of overweight and obesity of 20% sugar sweetened drink tax in UK: Econometric and comparative risk assessment modelling study|last2=Mytton|first2=O. T.|journal=BMJ|doi=10.1136/bmj.f6189|year=2013|volume=347|pages=f6189|pmc=3814405|pmid=24179043|last3=Kehlbacher|first3=A.|last4=Tiffin|first4=R.|last5=Rayner|first5=M.|last6=Scarborough|first6=P.|last1=Briggs|first1=A. D. M.}}</ref>

==== 評論 ====
加稅的決定受到了英國飲料生產商的批評，並被國會議員[[威爾·奎因斯|威爾·奎因斯]]描述為“保護，倒退和最壞的[[保姆國家|保姆國]]。”<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ft.com/intl/cms/s/0/5b41e47a-ec53-11e5-bb79-2303682345c8.html#axzz43HbjkDzd|script-title=en:UK tax on sugary drinks is ‘nannying’ and ‘impractical’|date=17 March 2016|publisher=Financial Times|last1=Neville|first1=Sarah|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2022-02-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220219051809/https://www.ft.com/content/5b41e47a-ec53-11e5-bb79-2303682345c8#axzz43HbjkDzd|dead-url=no}}</ref>

[[舊金山加利福尼亞大學|加利福尼亞大學舊金山分校]]醫學院的Robert Lustig教授說，英國的稅收措施可能無法長遠實行，「果汁應該像蘇打一樣徵稅，因為從代謝角度來看，果汁與蘇打水一樣 <ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.ft.com/intl/cms/s/0/311a74ec-ed24-11e5-888e-2eadd5fbc4a4.html?siteedition=intl|title=Robert Lustig: godfather of the sugar tax|date=18 March 2016|publisher=Financial Times|last1=Kaminska|first1=Izabella|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2022-02-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220219051740/https://www.ft.com/content/311a74ec-ed24-11e5-888e-2eadd5fbc4a4?siteedition=intl|dead-url=no}}</ref>。」政府在2016年初公佈的英國糖稅建議範圍狹窄，不針對純果汁和奶類飲料。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/health-35824071|title=Sugar tax: How it will work?|date=16 March 2016|publisher=BBC News|last1=Triggle|first1=Nick|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2020-09-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200921135200/https://www.bbc.com/news/health-35824071|dead-url=no}}</ref>

格拉斯哥大學的一項研究（其抽樣了132,000名成年人）發現，關注糖在隔離中誤導消費者減少脂肪攝入對減少肥胖也至關重要。<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gla.ac.uk/news/headline_474903_en.html|title=University of Glasgow - University news - Focusing on sugar in the fight against global obesity could be misleading|accessdate=2016-08-10|website=www.gla.ac.uk|archive-date=2017-01-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170105063809/http://www.gla.ac.uk/news/headline_474903_en.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 美國 ===
美國沒有全國性的蘇打水稅，但其中一些城市已經通過了各自的稅法，近年來在各個城市、州甚至在國會上對汽水加稅的辯論越來越多。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://qz.com/685327/the-fight-over-taxing-your-sugary-soda-just-kicked-into-high-gear/|title=SODA SCUFFLE: The fight over taxing your sugary soda just kicked into high gear|last=Purdy|first=Chase|date=17 May 2016|work=Quartz|accessdate=15 November 2016|deadurl=no|archive-date=2019-11-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191128132027/https://qz.com/685327/the-fight-over-taxing-your-sugary-soda-just-kicked-into-high-gear/}}</ref>
[[File:Sodas.JPG|缩略图]]
在2009年，僅在美國，[[美国的肥胖问题|與肥胖相關]]的醫療費用估計為每年1470億美元。同年，美國心臟協會報告說，軟飲料和糖份甜味飲料是美國人飲食中添加糖的最大來源。[[添加糖|添加糖]]是在加工或製備過程中添加到食物中的糖和糖漿，以及在餐桌上添加的糖和糖漿。過量攝取添加糖，此類與天然糖相反的糖，牽涉到肥胖率的上升。<ref>American Heart Association, [http://americanheart.mediaroom.com/index.php?s=43&item=800 statement], 24 August 2009, {{Wayback|url=http://americanheart.mediaroom.com/index.php?s=43&item=800 |date=20090828151637 }}</ref>

==== 美國地方與蘇打稅 ====
費城和伯克利是首兩個在美國通過含糖飲料稅的城市。 在課徵每盎司1美分的含糖飲料稅之後，伯克利的碳酸飲料消費量已下降超過五分之一。 費城每盎司1.5美分的稅將於2017年1月生效。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-soda-tax-idUSKCN12S200|title=First U.S. soda tax cuts consumption beyond expectations|accessdate=15 November 2016|date=28 October 2016|publisher=Reuters|deadurl=no|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108202111/https://www.reuters.com/article/us-health-soda-tax-idUSKCN12S200}}</ref>

===== 加州伯克利 =====
2014年11月4日，76％的伯克利選民批准了蘇打水徵稅方案中的D方案，並於2015年1月1日生效，成為美國的第一個這類稅法。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.berkeleyside.com/2014/11/04/berkeley-2014-elections-tune-in-here-for-live-coverage|title=Berkeley 2014 elections tune in here for live coverage|accessdate=7 November 2014|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141107012218/http://www.berkeleyside.com/2014/11/04/berkeley-2014-elections-tune-in-here-for-live-coverage/|archivedate=2014-11-07|deadurl=yes}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.npr.org/blogs/thesalt/2014/11/05/361793296/how-did-berkeley-pass-a-soda-tax-bloombergs-cash-didnt-hurt?utm_medium=RSS&utm_campaign=us|title=How Did Berkeley Pass A Soda Tax? Bloomberg's Cash Didn't Hurt|date=5 November 2014|publisher=NPR|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2015-03-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150330134324/http://www.npr.org/blogs/thesalt/2014/11/05/361793296/how-did-berkeley-pass-a-soda-tax-bloombergs-cash-didnt-hurt?utm_medium=RSS&utm_campaign=us|dead-url=no}}</ref> 該措施對指定的含糖飲料如蘇打水、運動飲料、能量飲料和甜味冰茶的分銷商徵收每盎司1美分的稅金，但不包括乳製品飲料、膳食替代飲料、低熱量蘇打水、果汁及酒精飲料。 
所產生的收入將進入伯克利市的普通基金。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ballotpedia.org/City_of_Berkeley_Sugary_Beverages_and_Soda_Tax_Question,_Measure_D_%28November_2014%29|title=City of Berkeley Sugary Beverages and Soda Tax Question, Measure D (November 2014)|work=ballotpedia.org|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2020-12-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201209083446/https://ballotpedia.org/City_of_Berkeley_Sugary_Beverages_and_Soda_Tax_Question,_Measure_D_(November_2014)|dead-url=no}}</ref> 在鄰近的舊金山，一個類似的措施獲得了54％的投票，但沒有通過所需的絕對多數。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://ballotpedia.org/City_of_San_Francisco_Sugary_Drink_Tax,_Proposition_E_%28November_2014%29|title=City of San Francisco Sugary Drink Tax, Proposition E (November 2014)|work=Ballotpedia|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111181419/https://ballotpedia.org/City_of_San_Francisco_Sugary_Drink_Tax,_Proposition_E_(November_2014)|dead-url=no}}</ref> 2015年8月，研究人員發現，法律規定的飲料的平均價格上漲幅度不到稅額的一半。 對於可口可樂和百事可樂，22％的稅款轉給了消費者，其餘由供應商支付。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.news.cornell.edu/stories/2015/08/study-berkeley-soda-tax-falls-flat|title=Study: Berkeley soda tax falls flat|accessdate=2015-08-25|date=17 August 2015|last=Boscia|first=Ted|publisher=Cornell University|website=Cornell Chronicle|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108101408/https://news.cornell.edu/stories/2015/08/study-berkeley-soda-tax-falls-flat|dead-url=no}}</ref> [[加州大學柏克萊分校|加州大學伯克利分校]]的研究人員發現該稅收的傳遞率比一般情況還高：47％的稅收被轉嫁至糖味飲料價格的上漲，其中69％被轉嫁到更高的蘇打水價格。<ref>Falbe, J., N. Rojas, et al. (2015). </ref> 2016年8月，加州大學伯克利分校的一項研究顯示，在城市低收入社區中，蘇打飲料和含糖飲料的飲酒量下降了21％。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.berkeley.edu/2016/08/23/sodadrinking/|title=Soda tax linked to drop in sugary beverage drinking in Berkeley|date=23 August 2016|publisher=UC Berkeley|first1=Yasmin|last1=Anwar|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2020-11-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201113204549/https://news.berkeley.edu/2016/08/23/sodadrinking/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

===== 費城 =====
民主黨費城市長吉姆·肯尼（Jim Kenney）提出了一個實行於全市的蘇打水稅，這將使蘇打水的價格以每盎司3美分的比例增加。 當時，這是美國最大的蘇打稅提案。  肯尼推動使用稅收收入來支持普遍的前幼兒園就學計畫、就業和發展計畫，他預計將在5年內籌集4億美元，同時藉此減少含糖飲料的需求來減少糖攝入量。肯尼的蘇打水稅提案被聚焦於全國注目之下，並造成了[[民主党_(美国)|民主黨]]內部主要成員的分歧。總統候選人[[伯尼·桑德斯|伯尼·桑德斯]]（Bernie Sanders）在一頁[[社论对页版|社論對頁版]]提出論辯，認為稅收會傷害窮人。<ref name="philly.com">{{cite web|url=http://articles.philly.com/2016-03-02/news/71101864_1_soda-tax-tax-proposal-proposed-sugary-drinks-tax|title=Kenney: Soda tax would fund $400M in projects|publisher=|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2016-09-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160920052119/http://articles.philly.com/2016-03-02/news/71101864_1_soda-tax-tax-proposal-proposed-sugary-drinks-tax|dead-url=no}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.phillymag.com/citified/2016/04/24/bernie-sanders-soda-tax-op-ed/|title=Bernie Sanders Op-Ed: A Soda Tax Would Hurt Philly's Poor|date=24 April 2016|publisher=|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2020-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201111214456/https://www.phillymag.com/citified/2016/04/24/bernie-sanders-soda-tax-op-ed/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 另一方面，他的對手[[希拉里·克林顿|希拉里·克林頓]]說她“非常支持”這個想法。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/04/21/politics/hillary-clinton-soda-tax-philadelphia/index.html|title=Clinton 'very supportive' of Philadelphia soda tax|last=CNN|first=David Wright|publisher=|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2020-11-08|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201108104325/https://www.cnn.com/2016/04/21/politics/hillary-clinton-soda-tax-philadelphia/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 由多家蘇打水公司和分銷商資助的美國飲料協會根據這個想法於各地的電視、廣播和報紙放送廣告，聲稱稅收將不成比例地傷害窮人。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://articles.philly.com/2016-03-07/news/71249958_1_beverage-industry-soda-tax-liberty-bell-beverage-pac|title=Soft drinks, hard lobbying|publisher=|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2016-10-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161005143746/http://articles.philly.com/2016-03-07/news/71249958_1_beverage-industry-soda-tax-liberty-bell-beverage-pac|dead-url=no}}</ref> 另一方面，美國心臟協會表示支持這種稅收。

費城市議會於2016年6月16日批准了每盎司1.5美分的稅。作為通過的折衷立法的一部分，該稅也將課徵於人工甜味飲料，如低熱量蘇打水。 該法將於2017年1月1日生效。<ref name="Nadolny">{{cite news|url=http://www.philly.com/philly/news/politics/20160617_Philadelphia_City_Council_to_vote_on_soda_tax.html|title=Soda tax passes; Philadelphia is first big city in nation to enact one|last=Nadolny|first=Tricia L.|date=16 June 2016|newspaper=[[The_Philadelphia_Enquirer|The Philadelphia Enquirer]]|accessdate=17 June 2016|archive-date=2019-04-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190401205949/https://www.philly.com/philly/news/politics/20160617_Philadelphia_City_Council_to_vote_on_soda_tax.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

===== 舊金山 =====
2016年11月8日，每盎司1％的蘇打水稅（第五方案）以超過61％之投票比例通過，並將於2018年1月1日適用於含糖飲料的分銷商。<ref name="auto">{{cite web|url=http://www.wsj.com/articles/soda-taxes-approved-in-four-cities-vote-looms-in-chicagos-cook-county-1478698979|title=Soda Taxes Approved in Four Cities, Vote Looms in Chicago’s Cook County|date=9 November 2016|last=Esterl|first=Mike|newspaper=Wall Street Journal|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2020-09-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200929224616/https://www.wsj.com/articles/soda-taxes-approved-in-four-cities-vote-looms-in-chicagos-cook-county-1478698979|dead-url=no}}</ref> 蘇打水業者花費近2000萬美元，仍無法成功打敗蘇打水稅倡議，其金額並創下了舊金山投票初步行動的紀錄。<ref name="KnightSF2016">{{cite news|url=http://www.sfchronicle.com/politics/article/Record-spending-by-soda-industry-to-defeat-Prop-V-10306250.php/|title=Record spending by soda industry to defeat Prop V|last=Knight|first=Heather|date=25 October 2016|work=San Francisco Chronicle|accessdate=2016-12-05|archive-date=2020-09-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200919133820/https://www.sfchronicle.com/politics/article/Record-spending-by-soda-industry-to-defeat-Prop-V-10306250.php|dead-url=no}}</ref>

